---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

// Services — three packages as plain articles, equal visual weight,
// no "best value" hierarchy. Pricing held for the Discovery Call.
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services"
  description="How Stacey works — the Discovery Call, what a session looks like, and the ways to work together."
>
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="process-heading">
    <div class="column">
      <h1 id="process-heading">How Stacey works</h1>

      <p>
        Every working relationship starts with a Discovery Call &mdash;
        free, about twenty minutes, no pressure to continue. You'll
        come away knowing whether you want to.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you keep going, the sessions feel like Grampy's kitchen
        table. Plain language, a few things at a time. Once those
        are clear the rest tends to settle.
      </p>

      <p>
        You leave with a clearer picture and one or two concrete
        next steps. The rest can wait until the next session.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="packages-heading">
    <div class="column-wide">
      <h2 id="packages-heading">Ways to work together</h2>

      <p>
        These are the ways Stacey commonly works with people. None is
        better than another &mdash; they're shaped to fit different lives.
      </p>

      <article style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        <h3>The Clarity Session</h3>
        <p>
          A single conversation. For people who want one clear look
          at their finances &mdash; accounts, income, what's owed, what
          they're hoping for &mdash; and want to leave with one or two
          concrete next steps. No ongoing commitment.
        </p>
        <p class="caption">
          Single session. Pricing on the Discovery Call.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        <h3>The Quarterly Check-In</h3>
        <p>
          For people who'd rather not sort through money alone four
          times a year. We pick up where we left off, look at what's
          changed, and adjust. Useful when life has more moving
          parts: couples, families, anyone caring for aging parents,
          anyone in transition.
        </p>
        <p class="caption">
          Recurring quarterly. Pricing on the Discovery Call.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        <h3>The Family Conversation</h3>
        <p>
          For families who want to talk about money together. Across
          generations, between couples, among siblings sorting out a
          parent's care. Stacey runs the conversation; the hard parts
          go better when someone steady is at the table.
        </p>
        <p class="caption">
          Custom scope. Pricing on the Discovery Call.
        </p>
      </article>

      <p style="margin-top: 4rem;">
        Not sure which fits? <a href="/contact">Book a Discovery Call</a>
        &mdash; that's what it's for.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="not-heading">
    <div class="column">
      <h2 id="not-heading">What this isn't</h2>

      <p>
        Stacey isn't a financial advisor or a registered investment
        advisor. She doesn't sell investment products. She doesn't
        manage your accounts or take a percentage of your assets.
      </p>

      <p>
        She charges a flat fee for her time. That's it. The
        relationship is between her and you, not her and a broker.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
